    public class Login
extends javax.swing.JButton
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener
    The Login class stores data associated with the user's authentication credentials (username, password, and user type level). It has the following fields 1) DB_URL; // Named constant for MySQL URL 2) USER_NAME; // Named constant for MySQL default username 3) PASSWORD; // Named constant for MySQL default password It has the following methods 1) Login() - constructor 2) getPanel() - This method returns the login panel 3) getUserType() - This method returns the user's UserLevelType value 4) actionPerformed(ActionEvent) - This method calls the ActionEvent when the user clicks a button
    Version:
